<html t:type="layout" title="Index" t:sidebarTitle="Things to do next" xmlns:t="http://tapestry.apache.org/schema/tapestry_5_1_0.xsd"
	xmlns:p="tapestry:parameter">
	<!-- Most of the page content, including <head>, <body>, etc. tags, comes from Layout.tml -->


	<p>
		<h2>Welcome to the Umbrella.</h2>
	</p>
	<p>
		The Umbrella is the Pan-European Identity System for Users of the European Photon / Neutron Facilities.
		<br />
		First time such kind of IT platform is offered:
		<ul>
			<li>
				<b>EU wide</b>
			</li>
			<li>
				<b>community overlapping</b>
			</li>
			<li>
				<b>shared between different EU Projects</b>
			</li>
		</ul>
	</p>
	<p>
		<h1>Umbrella Topology</h1>
		<br />
		<img src="/umbrella-start.png" />
	</p>
	<table border="0">
		<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<h1>Goal:</h1>
					<ul>
						<li>
							Optimisation of process from experimental
							data acquisition to data publication:
							<ul>
								<li>data acquisition</li>
								<li>data analysis</li>
								<li>data transfer</li>
								<li>trans-facility experiments</li>
								<li>remote data access</li>
								<li>remote experiment access</li>
							</ul>
						</li>
					</ul>
				</p>
			</td>
			<td>
				<p>
					<h1>Umbrella:</h1>
					<ul>
						<li>Provides an EU-wide, unique, persistent user ID</li>
						<li>Respects confidentiality</li>
						<li>Is a dedicated photon / neutron user federation</li>
						<li>Is based upon the local user office structure</li>
						<li>Users manage own entries, supervision by user offices</li>
						<li>Bridges to similar identification systems (Switch, EduGain, Grid)</li>
						<li>Platform was developed by PSI through EU projects: EuroFEL ESFRI project, PaNData ODI FP7, PaNData Europe, CRISP</li>
						<li>Start of implementation spring 2013</li>
					</ul>
				</p>
			</td>
		</tr>
	</table>
	<p>
		<h1>User benefits through common Umbrella user interface</h1>
		<ul>
			<li>Info &amp; service portal</li>
			<li>Remote experiment access (Moonshot)</li>
			<li>Remote file access (ICAT)</li>
		</ul>
	</p>
